parameters: Noble Tragos: Who the hell are you all!?

Clea: We are members of the Adventurer's Guild, from Ftera.
We have come this time not as representatives of the Guild,
but for personal reasons.

Noble Tragos: So it's you all... Because of you, my
relationship with Pido has been ruined!

Noble Tragos: But I have money... I have an infinite source
of money, the Crystal Mine!
Thief Nora: Do you remember the child of the beastman...?

Noble Tragos: Ah, Psema. I bought him from a man and kept
him as a pet. He's here!

Noble Tragos: You were a useless failure who couldn't even
learn words, but I wonder if you managed to remember some
basic prostitute-like language?

Noble Tragos: Well, you don't have time to choose means to
protect your lives that will definitely not be returned.

Noble Tragos: Even force can be bought with money. It's a
shame to kill such beautiful women, but I'll make sure you
die!
Thief Nora: Clea-san... Can I go all out?

Mage Relm: I didn't expect to encounter someone who
despises people to this extent. I will also give it my all.

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, I wonder if everyone feels the
same way?

Clea: I apologize to the hired individuals, but please step
back so that I can punch the person sitting in the back.

Noble Tragos: Th-Those are... former elite soldiers of the
Imperial Army...!

Clea: Are you going to buy us with money next? We will
absolutely not comply.

Noble Tragos: W-Wait! It's true that I had a daughter of a
beastman as a pet!

Noble Tragos: When I tried to sell them on the prostitution
island, they escaped from the carriage, it was an accident!

Noble Tragos: First of all, it's the fault of that merchant
Psema! He's the one who said he would sell me new beastmen,
so I...

Clea: Should I ask you one more time? We've only come here
to punch you away.

Noble Tragos: Hahaha! Can you hear it? The sound of the
mercenaries coming towards us!

Noble Tragos: I have always been victorious! Today is also
my victory, and from now on, forever and ever!

Captain Clevo: I don't remember being hired by scum like
you. So it was you after all, connected to Psema.

Cors the Wanderer: Oh, thanks to your strength, I was able
to come this far unscathed.

Noble Tragos: I-I remember you! You're the man from the
organization Mucos, won't you join forces with me?

Noble Tragos: Having a connection with the Crystal Mine...
It would be convenient for both your organization and
yourself, wouldn't it!?

Noble Tragos: Even if the conditions are somewhat
unfavorable now, I'll accept!

Thief Nora: That's enough... I didn't receive any words of
apology from you.

Noble Tragos: I-I will apologize! Letting the beastmen
escape resulted in a series of murders--

Thief Nora: What I want to hear is an apology to that
girl!
Thief Nora: That girl is not an animal!
Thief Nora: ...Huh, why are you here?

Cors the Wanderer: I used to boast about never being
stabbed in my line of work as a small-time thug.

Cors the Wanderer: ...Tragos-san, you know, I'm actually
from Oros.

Cors the Wanderer: I used to work in Tragos-san's owned
mine in the past, but after being conscripted, I've been
living in Mucos.

Noble Tragos: Do you understand the workings of the mine?!
And to go so far as to risk your life to help me!

Noble Tragos: I trust you! Let's earn together, everything
will go as we please!

Cors the Wanderer: This is a bright and nice place. On days
like this, it's good to drink wine and take a nap.

Noble Tragos: That's great! I have some excellent wine.
Let's treat your injuries--

Cors the Wanderer: Please, take a look while you can. I'm
going to die in a dirty place, not in such a beautiful place
like this.

Noble Tragos: W-What, is this loyalty to the
organization!?
Cors the Wanderer: I love the sea, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: Well, for those who want to hit this guy
without killing him, go ahead.

Captain Clevo: It seems that Pido from Camps was connected
to this. It's a gift from the comrades who died, please
accept it.
Clea: Please give your regards to all of us.

Thief Nora: She was a child whose name I didn't even know,
but she was definitely alive and trying to live!

Thief Nora: It's my frustration for not being able to save
that child...!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
